    "narrative": "The analytical priority for April 13th centers on capitalizing on high-ceiling matchups against soft-tossing lefties, which elevates **Corbin Carroll** to our premier start of the day at an 87.14 score. **Corbin Carroll** faces a favorable park environment coupled with an appealing matchup against Kremer, creating an optimal environment to hunt for stolen bases and extra-base hits. We are also leaning heavily into the Kikuchi stack; **Jose Caballero** (70.88) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (68.24) benefit significantly from the +8% SP skill adjustment and prevailing winds out. While **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (65.74) faces a slight penalty for the platoon disadvantage, his raw speed and aggressive base-running upside in this specific matchup make him a core contributor to our daily scarcity targets in the SB category.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Max Muncy**, who fell just short of the starting rotation with a score of 42.29. While **Max Muncy** benefits from the same park factors boosting **Tyler Soderstrom**, he is ultimately squeezed out due to a lower projected efficiency compared to our middle infield depth. The primary risk today involves the elevated SP skill of Skenes, which dampens the outlook for **James Wood** (49.62) and **Seiya Suzuki** (51.51); despite the favorable lineup spots, their projections are suppressed by the elite nature of their opponent. Furthermore, owners should monitor the lineup status for **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland**, as our projections are built on estimated batting order slots that could fluctuate, potentially impacting their already marginal scores of 45.05 and 52.91, respectively.",
